            . I am the wife of 
               <persName id="t18180909-303-person2098">
                  James 
                  Ward
               <interp inst="t18180909-303-person2098" type="surname" value="Ward"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18180909-303-person2098" type="given" value="James"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18180909-303-person2098" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , who is a <rs id="t18180909-303-viclabel1669" type="occupation">baker</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18180909-303-victim2096 t18180909-303-viclabel1669"></join>, and lives in York-street, Westminster, the prisoner was our <rs id="t18180909-303-deflabel1670" type="occupation">servant</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18180909-303-defend2095 t18180909-303-deflabel1670"></join>. On the 29th of May, I sent him with thirty-six quarterns and fifty half-quartern loaves to Mr. Small, Knightsbridge. I always enter them in a book, which he took with him. On examining the book next morning, I found the thirty-six altered to thirty. Mrs. Small had given him a receipt for thirty loaves. I charged him with it, he denied it, but afterwards said he would pay for them if I would say nothing about it. I told him I would send for an officer when my husband came home-this was on Saturday; he left, and never returned till Sunday morning, when he came for his wages.</p>
               <p>
                  <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="181809090095"></xptr>Prisoner. Q.Did you count the bread - A. Yes.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18180909-303-person2099">
                  MARY 
                  SMALL
               <interp inst="t18180909-303-person2099" type="surname" value="SMALL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18180909-303-person2099" type="given" value="MARY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18180909-303-person2099" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I keep a chandler's shop at Knights-bridge. On the 29th of May the prisoner brought me fifty half-quartern loaves and only thirty quarterns. He entered them in my book as thirty.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I only took thirty.</p>
